verbs.description: The European Union [V: will] start imposing duties on a list of U.S. products as of Friday in response to President Donald Trump 's decision to slap tariffs on steel and aluminum imports from Europe . The 28-nation EU was first expected to do so only next month but EU Trade Commissioner Cecilia Malmstrom said they would introduce " rebalancing " tariffs on about 2.8 billion euros ' ( $ 3.4 billion ) worth of U.S. products this week .
